---
By: E. Stanley Jones
Locus:
  Page: 172
  Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Freedom
---
No man is free until he is free at the center. When he lets go there, he is
free indeed. When the self is renounced, then one stands utterly
disillusioned, apart, asking for nothing. ...If anything comes to him, it
is all sheer gain. Then life becomes one constant surprise.
